FBIS4-48314 "drafr095_c_94037" FBIS-AFR-94-095 Daily Report 14 May 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA Western Cape Premier Announces Official Languages Western Cape Premier Announces Official Languages MB1405123794 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in English 1100 GMT 14 May 94 MB1405123794 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network English BFN [Text] The official languages of the western Cape region will be English, Afrikaans, and Xhosa. This was announced by provincial premier, Hernus Kriel, at a reception at the former administrator's residence in Cape Town. He said that the Western Cape Provincial Assembly would begin its work on the first of August.
